## Data pipeline — ISRO first

The single biggest signal to judges is which satellites you cite. Build your pipeline in this priority order:

**Resourcesat-2/2A** (LISS-IV at 5.8m) for high-resolution urban land use classification — buildings, bare soil, vegetation, water bodies, roads. This is your primary spatial layer.

**INSAT-3D/3DR** for thermal infrared. You pull the 4km thermal channel to get LST at diurnal intervals (day + night passes). This is your primary heat signal. ISRO data, ISRO judges, ISRO hackathon.

**Cartosat-2 series** (0.65m panchromatic) for building footprint extraction. Feed this into a U-Net to extract building outlines automatically — you'll need these for the GNN.

**BHUVAN geoportal** (bhuvan.nrsc.gov.in) is ISRO's own GIS platform. Pull thematic layers from here: urban sprawl, land use, drainage. Reference it explicitly in your presentation.

**Supplementary:** Landsat-9 Band 10/11 (thermal) for multi-temporal time series going back years. Sentinel-2 (10m multispectral) for fine-grained NDVI and NDWI. ERA5 reanalysis for wind speed, humidity, air temperature — these are your meteorological covariates.

**Ground truth:** IMD's automatic weather station data for validation. OpenStreetMap for street network topology (your GNN edge set). Census ward-level population data for the vulnerability index.

